historic talks\nL37: in Washington.\nL38: \nL39: \" data-post-id=\"0000019d-9492-daa9-a19f-96bbd12b0000\"\nL40: data-posted-date-timestamp=\"1776314200801\" data-seconds-delta-text=\"sec ago\"\nL41: data-minutes-delta-text=\"min ago\" data-hours-delta-text=\"h ago\"\u003e\nL42: \nL43: ## Chinese foreign minister says reopening of Hormuz an international demand\nL44: \nL45: Chinese Foreign Minister Wang Yi told his Iranian counterpart that reopening the\nL46: Strait of Hormuz was a unanimous demand from the international community.\nL47: \nL48: Wang Yi told Iran’s Foreign Minister Abbas Araghchi in a phone call that\nL49: Iran’s sovereignty, security, and legitimate rights should be respected as a\nL50: littoral state of the Strait of Hormuz, but freedom of navigation and safety\nL51: through the strait should be ensured.\nL52: \nL53: “Working to resume normal passage of the strait is a unanimous call from the\nL54: international community,” Wang was quoted as saying in a government statement\nL55: late Wednesday.\nL56: \nL57: Wang noted that the current situation had reached a critical juncture between war\nL58: and peace and also said that the window of peace was opening .\nL59: \nL60: \" data-post-id=\"0000019d-9491-d837-a3dd-beff6db50000\"\nL61: data-posted-date-timestamp=\"1776314141032\" data-seconds-delta-text=\"sec ago\"\nL62: data-minutes-delta-text=\"min ago\" data-hours-delta-text=\"h ago\"\u003e\nL63: \nL64: ## Trump says leaders of Lebanon and Israel to speak\nL65: \nL66: Trump wrote late Wednesday on Truth Social that leaders from Israel and Lebanon\nL67: would speak the next day in a renewed effort to broker a ceasefire after the\nL68: countries’ 【6†first direct talks】in decades ended the previous day in\nL69: Washington without a deal. It was not clear what leaders Trump was referring to.\nL70: The Israeli prime minister’s office did not immediately respond for comment,\nL71: which was posted before dawn in Israel and Lebanon.\nL72: \nL73: 1 New Story