data: {"type":"response.output_item.done","sequence_number":1066,"output_index":41,"item":{"type":"mcp_call","id":"mcpc_01kpag1ym2fxhsd6bnfw4rykgx","status":"completed","server_label":"browser","name":"open","arguments":"{\"cursor\": 8, \"id\": 1}","approval_request_id":null,"output":"L0: \nL1: URL:\nL2: https://www.mediaite.com/media/news/breaking-us-and-iran-reportedly-reach-in-principle-agreement-to-extend-ceasefire/\nL3: US-Iran Reach 'In Principle' Deal to Extend Ceasefire: AP\nL4: \nL5: # BREAKING: US and Iran Reportedly Reach ‘In Principle Agreement’ to Extend\nL6: Ceasefire\nL7: \nL8: 【0†Joe DePaolo】Apr 15th, 2026, 7:46 am\nL9: \nL10: Share\nL11: \nL12: Copy Link\nL13: \nL14: Protestors wave flags near the White House in Washington, Tuesday evening, April\nL15: 7, 2026. (AP Photo/J. Scott Applewhite)\nL16: \nL17: Just days after 【1†the collapse of marathon talks in Pakistan】, the U.S.\nL18: and Iran have reportedly reached an “in principle agreement” to extend the\nL19: ceasefire.\nL20: \nL21: 【2†According to the Associated Press†apnews.com】, which cites unnamed\nL22: regional officials, the two sides have struck a deal in principle despite the\nL23: naval blockade announced by President Donald Trump on Sunday, and renewed threats\nL24: from Iran.\nL25: \nL26: As of now, the two-week ceasefire is set to expire on April 22.\nL27: \nL28: “The U.S. blockade on Iranian ports and renewed Iranian threats have imperiled\nL29: the week-old agreement, but regional officials said Wednesday they were making\nL30: progress, telling The Associated Press that the United States and Iran had given\nL31: an ‘in principle agreement’ to extend it to allow for more diplomacy,”\nL32: according to AP reporters Samy Magdy, Sam Mets, and Munir Ahmed.\nL33: \nL34: In 【3†an interview on Fox Business†www.foxbusiness.com】with Maria\nL35: Bartiromo, which was taped Tuesday, the president expressed optimism that the\nL36: conflict is on the verge of ending.\nL37: \nL38: “I think it’s close to over, yeah,” Trump said. “I view it as very close\nL39: to over.”\nL40: \nL41: In a 【1†separate interview with the New York Post】, Trump advised reporter\nL42: Caitlin Doornbos — who is in Islamabad, Pakistan, after having covered the\nL43: US-Iran peace negotiations over the weekend — that she should remain there to\nL44: cover subsequent talks.\nL45: \nL46: “You should stay there, really, because something could be happening over the\nL47: next two days, and we’re more inclined to go there,” Trump said of Islamabad.\nL48: \nL49: This story is breaking.\nL50: \nL51: New: The Mediaite One-Sheet \"Newsletter of Newsletters\"Your daily summary and\nL52: analysis of what the many, many media newsletters are saying and reporting.\nL53: 【4†Subscribe now!】\nL54: \nL55: 【5†Previous Post】【6†Next Post】\nL56: \nL57: 【5†Previous Post】【6†Next Post】\nL58: \nL59: Joe DePaolo - Editor in Chief\nL60: \nL61: Joe DePaolo is the Editor in Chief of Mediaite. Email him here: joed@mediaite.com\nL62: Follow him on X: @joe\\_depaolo\nL63: \nL64: * * *\nL65: \nL66: ## Comments\nL67: \nL68: ↓ Scroll down for comments ↓\nL69: \nL70: Loading comments..."}}

