officials hoping for more\nL12: US-Iran talks\nL13: \nL14: Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent warns that the US is preparing to ramp up\nL15: economic pain on Iran by levying secondary sanctions on financial institutions\nL16: that do business with Tehran. He says it is the “financial equivalent” of the\nL17: bombing campaign.\nL18: \nL19: Edited By 【0†PATRICK QUINN】and 【1†BRIAN P. D. HANNON】\nL20: \nL21: Major developments we’re following:\nL22: \nL23: - 【2†Pakistan’s army chief met Wednesday in Tehran】with Iran’s foreign\nL24: minister in the latest diplomatic move to ease tensions in the Middle East and\nL25: arrange a second round of negotiations between the United States and Iran after\nL26: 【3†almost seven weeks of war】.\nL27: \nL28: - U.S. Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent warned on Wednesday that the 【4†U.S.\nL29: is preparing to ramp up economic pain on Iran】by levying secondary sanctions on\nL30: financial institutions that do business with the Middle Eastern nation. Bessent\nL31: called the measure the “financial equivalent” of a bombing campaign.\nL32: \nL33: - The 【5†Israeli military killed four Lebanese rescue workers and wounded six\nL34: others in three consecutive, targeted strikes】Wednesday, paramedic groups said,\nL35: a stark illustration of the human cost of the Israeli military campaign against\nL36: Hezbollah in southern Lebanon a day after the two countries held historic talks\nL37: in Washington.\nL38: \nL39: \" data-post-id=\"0000019d-9492-daa9-a19f-96bbd12b0000\"\nL40: data-posted-date-timestamp=\"1776314200801\" data-seconds-delta-text=\"sec ago\"\nL41: data-minutes-delta-text=\"min ago\" data-hours-delta-text=\"h ago\"\u003e\nL42: \nL43: ## Chinese foreign minister says reopening of Hormuz an international demand\nL44: \nL45: Chinese Foreign Minister Wang Yi told his Iranian counterpart that reopening the\nL46: Strait of Hormuz was a unanimous demand from the international community.\nL47: \nL48: Wang Yi told Iran’s Foreign Minister Abbas Araghchi in a phone call that\nL49: Iran’s sovereignty, security, and legitimate rights should be respected as a\nL50: littoral state of the Strait of Hormuz, but freedom of navigation and safety\nL51: through the strait should be ensured.\nL52: \nL53: “Working to resume normal passage of the strait is a unanimous call from the\nL54: international community,” Wang was quoted as saying in a government statement\nL55: late Wednesday.\nL56: \nL57: Wang noted that the current situation had reached a critical juncture between war\nL58: and peace and also said that the window of peace was opening .\nL59: \nL60: \" data-post-id=\"0000019d-9491-d837-a3dd-beff6db50000\"\nL61: data-posted-date-timestamp=\"1776314141032\" data-seconds-delta-text=\"sec ago\"\nL62: data-minutes-delta-text=\"min ago\" data-hours-delta-text=\"h ago\"\u003e\nL63: \nL64: ## Trump says leaders of Lebanon and Israel to speak\nL65: \nL66: Trump wrote late Wednesday on Truth Social that leaders from Israel and Lebanon\nL67: would speak the next day in a renewed effort to broker a ceasefire after the\nL68: countries’ 【6†first direct talks】in decades ended the previous day in\nL69: Washington without a deal. It was not clear what leaders Trump was referring to.\nL70: The Israeli prime minister’s office did not immediately respond for comment,\nL71: which was posted before dawn in Israel and Lebanon.\nL72: \nL73: 1 New Story"},{"type":"mcp_call","id":"mcpc_01kpag1pdmfv2v043b8gza347t","status":"completed","server_label":"browser","name":"open","arguments":"{\"cursor\": 5, \"id\": 7}","approval_request_id":null,"output":""},{"type":"mcp_call","id":"mcpc_01kpag1peyfv2v3dpt6yem7510","status":"completed","server_label":"browser","name":"open","arguments":"{\"cursor\": 5, \"id\": 7}","approval_request_id":null,"output":"L0: \nL1: URL: https://www.reuters.com/world/us/crisis-point-2026-04-09/\nL2: Iran war tests Trump’s most enduring political gifts \\| Reuters\nL3: \nL4: 【0†Exclusive news, data and analytics for financial market professionalsLearn\nL5: more aboutRefinitiv】\nL6: \nL7: People walk next to a mural depicting the late leader of the Islamic Revolution\nL8: Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini and the late Supreme Leader of Iran Ayatollah Ali\nL9: Khamenei, after U.S. President... 【1†Purchase Licensing Rights, opens new\nL10: tab†www.reutersconnect.com】Read more\nL11: \nL12: April 9 - The Iran war is ending. Or so the White House says. The last-minute\nL13: ceasefire this week in a conflict that has convulsed capitals from Washington to\nL14: Brussels to Tehran has left several key issues up in the air. What does it mean\nL15: politically? And will it last?\nL16: \nL17: Last week, President Donald Trump stepped inside a Washington theater, the lights\nL18: dimmed and Broadway performers crooned about how to wow an audience.\nL19: \nL20: “Razzle dazzle 'em, and they'll beg you for more,” goes one of the songs,\nL21: from “Chicago.” “Give 'em an ‌act with lots of flash in it, and the\nL22: reaction will be passionate.”\nL23: \nL24: It’s not clear what Trump may have taken from the Jazz Age musical. But\nL25: Trump’s own mastery of spectacle has been key to his decades in public life.\nL26: \nL27: It’s a political gift being tested by a war with Iran that has 【2†divided\nL28: the nation】, his political base and the 【3†NATO alliance】.\nL29: \nL30: Trump again demonstrated his ability to dominate the public conversation this\nL31: week. His press conference on Monday refocused attention on the war to 【4†a\nL32: daring rescue】of an airman stranded deep inside enemy territory.\nL33: \nL34: His 【5†profanity-laced tirade】on 【6†Easter】and his later\nL35: 【7†eleventh-hour decision】to call off what he described as a\nL36: civilization-ending attack on Iran transfixed and alarmed people around the\nL37: globe. A Trump administration official told my colleague that ⁠Trump’s most\nL38: charged rhetoric 【8†came from the president himself】as he sought to create\nL39: leverage through unpredictability.\nL40: \nL41: The president’s ability to control the facts on the ground has been far more\nL42: tenuous than his ability to shape the narrative. Despite achieving tactical\nL43: military wins in Iran, the United States could still fall short of his declared\nL44: goals.\nL45: \nL46: In the two days since Trump declared the ceasefire, no one has released a\nL47: comprehensive document detailing the agreement’s terms. Neither side agrees on\nL48: what the deal is precisely. Iran has not publicly conceded Washington’s key\nL49: demands and the Strait of Hormuz is not fully open to traffic. Tehran has not\nL50: publicly agreed to halt its nuclear program nor to stop arming groups abroad.\nL51: \nL52: At home, Americans remain skeptical of a war that has dragged into a sixth week\nL53: and further eroded Trump’s job approval rating. 【9†U.S. gas prices】are\nL54: set to remain elevated through the crucial summertime driving season.\nL55: \nL56: The unfinished work in the Middle East has exposed the limits – and risks - of\nL57: 【10†Trump’s strategy】of making apocalyptic threats and backing down.\nL58: Critics mocked what they saw as another example of “TACO,” or “Trump always\nL59: chickens out,” and even some of Trump's fellow Republicans openly expressed\nL60: concern about the president’s chilling rhetoric.\nL61: \nL62: There’s no ‌doubt that ⁠Trump’s showmanship can control attention. But as\nL63: the gap between his rhetoric and an unstable Middle East expands, he may leave\nL64: his audience asking what’s real.\nL65: \nL66: ## TOP US POLITICS HEADLINES\nL67: \nL68: 【9†US pump prices to stay elevated despite US-Iran ceasefire deal, market\nL69: observers say】\nL70: \nL71: 【10†Trump's abrupt Iran reversal exposes limits of his leverage】\nL72: \nL73: 【11†Evangelicals amplify Trump's religious framing of Iran war】\nL74: \nL75: 【12†Draw it yourself: Checking Trump’s tariff claims a year later】\nL76: \nL77: 【4†Trump seizes on rescue of downed airman to recast unpopular Iran war】\nL78: \nL79: ## CHART OF THE WEEK\nL80: \nL81: Stacked bar chart showing a majority of Americans worry about the Iran war's\nL82: impact on their personal finances and more generally about the financial costs of\nL83: military action in Iran.\nL84: \nL85: ## THE VIEW FROM BEIRUT\nL86: \nL87: What ceasefire? That’s a question on the minds of residents of Lebanon. The\nL88: two-week truce in the Iran war has provided no end to an 【13†Israeli bombing\nL89: campaign there】. Both Iran ⁠and ceasefire mediator Pakistan understood that\nL90: the ceasefire agreement included Lebanon, where Iran’s Hezbollah allies are\nL91: entrenched. The White House and Israel said that was not the case.\nL92: \nL93: If the ceasefire agreement unravels, Lebanon may be the reason. Israeli Prime\nL94: Minister Benjamin Netanyahu sees Iran and affiliated groups across the region as\nL95: in retreat but not fully defeated. By creating \"buffer zones\" in Gaza, Syria and\nL96: Lebanon, he hopes to push them back as far as ⁠possible. But it also means\nL97: 【14†a semi-permanent state of war】, Israeli military and defense officials\nL98: told my colleagues in Jerusalem. Washington may be dragged back into the Middle\nL99: East for years to come.\nL100: \nL101: ## WHAT TO WATCH FOR\nL102: \nL103: April 9: Rev. Al Sharpton's National Action Network hosts potential 2028\nL104: Democratic candidates\nL105: \nL106: April 11: US, Iran may meet for negotiations in Islamabad\nL107: \nL108: April 13: Trump meets with Dutch King Willem-Alexander\nL109: \nL110: April 16: Election to fill seat ⁠vacated by New Jersey Governor Mikie Sherrill\nL111: (NJ-11)\nL112: \nL113: April 17: Trump speaks at Turning Point USA event in Phoenix\nL114: \nL115: ## THE WHO, WHAT AND WHEN\nL116: \nL117: 【15†Highs and lows from the US jobs report】\nL118: \nL119: 【16†Can the US and Iran bridge their differences in talks?】\nL120: \nL121: 【17†Trump’s mixed messages and Iran’s bombs kept the Kurds out of the\nL122: war】\nL123: \nL124: Reporting by Trevor Hunnicutt; Editing by Colleen Jenkins and Alistair Bell\nL125: \nL126: Our Standards: 【18†The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles., opens new\nL127: tab†www.thomsonreuters.com】\nL128: \nL129: Thomson Reuters\nL130: \nL131: Trevor Hunnicutt is White House Correspondent at Reuters News. He writes about\nL132: U.S. foreign and domestic policy and regularly travels with the President of the\nL133: United States. Prior to joining the White House team in 2021, he covered\nL134: presidential campaigns, economics, finance and investing for many years. He has\nL135: also served on the board of the White House Correspondents' Association.\nL136: Hunnicutt holds a bachelor's degree from Pomona College and a master's from the\nL137: London School of Economics.\nL138: \nL139: ## World\nL140: \nL141: ### Former Brazil spy chief freed in the US after ICE detention, Bolsonaro ally\nL142: says\nL143: \nL144: 【19†Americascategory】· April 15, 2026 · 10:59 PM UTC · ago\nL145: \nL146: Former Brazilian intelligence chief Alexandre Ramagem has ‌been freed in the\nL147: United States, said Paulo Figueiredo, an ally of former President Jair\nL148: ⁠Bolsonaro who lives in the U.S., on Wednesday.\nL149: \nL150: 【20†United Statescategory】【21†Mamdani, Hochul propose tax on New York\nL151: second homes worth more than $5 million】\nL152: \nL153: 【22†Businesscategory】【23†Ukraine official expects US-Ukrainian\nL154: investment fund to approve second project in summer】\nL155: \nL156: 【24†Worldcategory】【25†Mark Mobius, 'Indiana Jones of emerging markets,'\nL157: dies at 89】\nL158: \nL159: 【24†Worldcategory】【26†Scenes from Coachella】"},{"type":"mcp_call","id":"mcpc_01kpag1r0tfvg9y8ps3m8m9eyx","status":"completed","server_label":"browser","name":"open","arguments":"{\"cursor\": 6, \"loc\": 24, \"num_lines\": 10}","approval_request_id":null,"output":""},{"type":"mcp_call","id":"mcpc_01kpag1r0tfvgrzq6vptmjff0n","status":"completed","server_label":"browser","name":"open","arguments":"{\"cursor\": 6, \"loc\": 24, \"num_lines\": 10}","approval_request_id":null,"output":"L24: - Proposed 'Islamabad Accord' for settlement\nL25: \nL26: April 6 (Reuters) - Iran and the United States have received a plan to end\nL27: hostilities that could come into effect on Monday and ‌reopen the Strait of\nL28: Hormuz, a source aware of the proposals said on Monday.\nL29: \nL30: A framework to end hostilities has been put together by Pakistan and exchanged\nL31: with Iran and the U.S. overnight, the source said, outlining a two-tier approach\nL32: with an immediate ceasefire followed by a comprehensive agreement.\nL33: "},{"type":"mcp_call","id":"mcpc_01kpag1s80fvnvp7jjg93za9nt","status":"completed","server_label":"browser","name":"open","arguments":"{\"cursor\": 7, \"loc\": 18, \"num_lines\": 10}","approval_request_id":null,"output":""},{"type":"mcp_call","id":"mcpc_01kpag1s80fvp81039vqdy669g","status":"completed","server_label":"browser","name":"open","arguments":"{\"cursor\": 7, \"loc\": 18, \"num_lines\": 10}","approval_request_id":null,"output":"L18: \nL19: - Trump's earlier threat draws international condemnation\nL20: \nL21: WASHINGTON/DUBAI/CAIRO, April 7 (Reuters) - U.S. President Donald Trump agreed to\nL22: a two-week ceasefire with Iran on Tuesday, less than two hours before his\nL23: deadline for Tehran to reopen the Strait of Hormuz or face devastating attacks on\nL24: its civilian infrastructure.\nL25: \nL26: Trump's announcement on social media represented an abrupt turnaround from\nL27: earlier in the day, when he issued an extraordinary warning that \"a whole"},{"type":"mcp_call","id":"mcpc_01kpag1thrfw08d2c82wrgggz9","status":"completed","server_label":"browser","name":"open","arguments":"{\"cursor\": 4, \"loc\": 10, \"num_lines\": 10}","approval_request_id":null,"output":""},{"type":"mcp_call","id":"mcpc_01kpag1thrfw0t8kk0vp3hn39w","status":"completed","server_label":"browser","name":"open","arguments":"{\"cursor\": 4, \"loc\": 10, \"num_lines\": 10}","approval_request_id":null,"output":"L10: 【1†Terug naar de krant】\nL11: \nL12: Het straatbeeld in Iran komt langzaam weer tot leven, sinds vorige week woensdag\nL13: het staakt-het-vuren met de Verenigde Staten inging. In Teheran zijn de kraampjes\nL14: terug, de straten druk. Voor het eerst in veertig dagen reed een vertaalster (40)\nL15: uit de hoofdstad afgelopen weekend met haar ouders een rondje door de wijk. Ze\nL16: wilden de militaire gebouwen zien die waren geraakt. „Ze zijn volledig met de\nL17: grond gelijk gemaakt”, vertelt ze aan NRC.\nL18: \nL19: Begin vorige week kwam al het werkende leven in Iran weer op gang. Kantoren zijn"},{"type":"mcp_call","id":"mcpc_01kpag1vspfwtvvqggpasd8jrg","status":"completed","server_label":"browser","name":"open","arguments":"{\"cursor\": 9, \"loc\": 22, \"num_lines\": 10}","approval_request_id":null,"output":""},{"type":"mcp_call","id":"mcpc_01kpag1vspfwvbakm142v2da4z","status":"completed","server_label":"browser","name":"open","arguments":"{\"cursor\": 9, \"loc\": 22, \"num_lines\": 10}","approval_request_id":null,"output":"invalid location parameter: 22. Cannot exceed page maximum of 14"},{"type":"mcp_call","id":"mcpc_01kpag1w1mfwybme2jnsmdrzp8","status":"completed","server_label":"browser","name":"open","arguments":"{\"cursor\": 9, \"loc\": 18}","approval_request_id":null,"output":""},{"type":"mcp_call","id":"mcpc_01kpag1w1mfwyr164d8mawfh3g","status":"completed","server_label":"browser","name":"open","arguments":"{\"cursor\": 9, \"loc\": 18}","approval_request_id":null,"output":"invalid location parameter: 18. Cannot exceed page maximum of 14"},{"type":"mcp_call","id":"mcpc_01kpag1x9afx9s48c83evdcmks","status":"completed","server_label":"browser","name":"find","arguments":"{\"cursor\": 9, \"pattern\": \"Pakistan\"}","approval_request_id":null,"output":""},{"type":"mcp_call","id":"mcpc_01kpag1x9afxaa7xw0k0m5h05g","status":"completed","server_label":"browser","name":"find","arguments":"{\"cursor\": 9, \"pattern\": \"Pakistan\"}","approval_request_id":null,"output":"No `find` results for pattern: `Pakistan`"},{"type":"mcp_call","id":"mcpc_01kpag1yjyfxhtpaa0ns17a9az","status":"completed","server_label":"browser","name":"open","arguments":"{\"cursor\": 8, \"id\": 1}","approval_request_id":null,"output":""},{"type":"mcp_call","id":"mcpc_01kpag1ym2fxhsd6bnfw4rykgx","status":"completed","server_label":"browser","name":"open","arguments":"{\"cursor\": 8, \"id\": 1}","approval_request_id":null,"output":"L0: \nL1: URL:\nL2: https://www.mediaite.com/media/news/breaking-us-and-iran-reportedly-reach-in-principle-agreement-to-extend-ceasefire/\nL3: US-Iran Reach 'In Principle' Deal to Extend Ceasefire: AP\nL4: \nL5: # BREAKING: US and Iran Reportedly Reach ‘In Principle Agreement’ to Extend\nL6: Ceasefire\nL7: \nL8: 【0†Joe DePaolo】Apr 15th, 2026, 7:46 am\nL9: \nL10: Share\nL11: \nL12: Copy Link\nL13: \nL14: Protestors wave flags near the White House in Washington, Tuesday evening, April\nL15: 7, 2026. (AP Photo/J. Scott Applewhite)\nL16: \nL17: Just days after 【1†the collapse of marathon talks in Pakistan】, the U.S.\nL18: and Iran have reportedly reached an “in principle agreement” to extend the\nL19: ceasefire.\nL20: \nL21: 【2†According to the Associated Press†apnews.com】, which cites unnamed\nL22: regional officials, the two sides have struck a deal in principle despite the\nL23: naval blockade announced by President Donald Trump on Sunday, and renewed threats\nL24: from Iran.\nL25: \nL26: As of now, the two-week ceasefire is set to expire on April 22.\nL27: \nL28: “The U.S. blockade on Iranian ports and renewed Iranian threats have imperiled\nL29: the week-old agreement, but regional officials said Wednesday they were making\nL30: progress, telling The Associated Press that the United States and Iran had given\nL31: an ‘in principle agreement’ to extend it to allow for more diplomacy,”\nL32: according to AP reporters Samy Magdy, Sam Mets, and Munir Ahmed.\nL33: \nL34: In 【3†an interview on Fox Business†www.foxbusiness.com】with Maria\nL35: Bartiromo, which was taped Tuesday, the president expressed optimism that the\nL36: conflict is on the verge of ending.\nL37: \nL38: “I think it’s close to over, yeah,” Trump said. “I view it as very close\nL39: to over.”\nL40: \nL41: In a 【1†separate interview with the New York Post】, Trump advised reporter\nL42: Caitlin Doornbos — who is in Islamabad, Pakistan, after having covered the\nL43: US-Iran peace negotiations over the weekend — that she should remain there to\nL44: cover subsequent talks.\nL45: \nL46: “You should stay there, really, because something could be happening over the\nL47: next two days, and we’re more inclined to go there,” Trump said of Islamabad.\nL48: \nL49: This story is breaking.\nL50: \nL51: New: The Mediaite One-Sheet \"Newsletter of Newsletters\"Your daily summary and\nL52: analysis of what the many, many media newsletters are saying and reporting.\nL53: 【4†Subscribe now!】\nL54: \nL55: 【5†Previous Post】【6†Next Post】\nL56: \nL57: 【5†Previous Post】【6†Next Post】\nL58: \nL59: Joe DePaolo - Editor in Chief\nL60: \nL61: Joe DePaolo is the Editor in Chief of Mediaite. Email him here: joed@mediaite.com\nL62: Follow him on X: @joe\\_depaolo\nL63: \nL64: * * *\nL65: \nL66: ## Comments\nL67: \nL68: ↓ Scroll down for comments ↓\nL69: \nL70: Loading comments..."},{"type":"message","id":"msg_01kpag202tfy09jabvc5m4e2fm","status":"completed","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"output_text","text":"**Laatste nieuws over de oorlog in Iran (per 16 april 2026)**  \n\n| Datum | Kerngebeurtenis | Samenvatting | Bron |\n|-------|-----------------|--------------|------|\n| 28 feb 2026 | **Operation Epic Fury** | Amerikaanse‑Israëlische luchtaanvallen in Iran, waaronder het vermoorden van de hoogste leiders van de Iraanse regering. | 2026‑Iran‑war artikel van Britannica【2†L31-L38】 |\n| 6 apr 2026 | **Pakistaanse bemiddeling** | Een door Pakistan opgesteld plan om een onmiddellijke wapenstilstand te bereiken, gevolgd door een uitgebreid akkoord. | Reuters, 6 apr 2026【6†L26-L32】 |\n| 7 apr 2026 | **Trump‑ceasefire** | President Trump kondigt een tweewekelijkse wapenstilstand aan, kort voor zijn deadline voor de heropening van de Straat van Hormuz. | Reuters, 7 apr 2026【7†L21-L24】 |\n| 15 apr 2026 | **NRC‑artikel “Dagelijks leven”** | Het dagelijks leven in Teheran herstelt na de wapenstilstand; inflatie stijgt, infrastructuur is nog steeds beschadigd. | NRC, 15 apr 2026【4†L12-L18】 |\n| 15 apr 2026 | **Reutersthema “Iran‑war tests Trump’s political gifts”** | Analyse van de politieke implicaties van de wapenstilstand en de resterende onduidelijkheden. | Reuters, 9 apr 2026 (referentie naar 15 apr)【10†L12-L15】 |\n| 15 apr 2026 | **Mediaite “In principle agreement”** | U.S. en Iran hebben een “in‑principle” akkoord bereikt om de wapenstilstand te verlengen tot 22 apr. | Mediaite, 15 apr 2026【11†L14-L30】 |\n| 16 apr 2026 | **AP live‑updates** | Pakistaanse delegatie ontmoet Iraanse functionarissen; Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent waarschuwt voor economische sancties; Chinese minister benadrukt noodzaak om de Straat van Hormuz te openen. | AP, 16 apr 2026 (live updates)【9†L12-L30】【9†L43-L48】 |\n\n**Belangrijkste ontwikkelingen in korte samenvatting**\n\n- **Ceasefire**: Sinds 7 apr. 2026 is er een tweewekelijkse wapenstilstand in werking, met de bedoeling om de Straat van Hormuz te heropenen. Er wordt gewerkt aan een uitgebreider, permanente overeenkomst (Pakistan, China, VS, Iran).\n- **Diplomatieke onderhandelingen**: Pakistaanse en Chinese diplomaten spelen een cruciale rol in de bemiddeling. De Verenigde Staten hebben aangekondigd de sancties op te schalen als Iran niet voldoet.\n- **Humanitaire situatie**: Ondanks het einde van de directe strijd, blijven er aanzienlijke civiele verliezen, infrastructuurbeschadigingen en economische problemen (inflatie, voedseltekorten) in Iran.\n- **Regionale impact**: De oorlog heeft geleid tot verhoogde spanningen in Libanon (Hezbollah‑Iran band), de Golf en de Middellandse Zee, en heeft de wereldwijde olie- en energieprijzen beïnvloed.\n\nDeze informatie geeft een actueel overzicht van de oorlog in Iran tot en met de laatste updates op 16 april 2026.","annotations":[],"logprobs":[]}]}],"previous_response_id":null,"model":"openai/gpt-oss-20b","reasoning":{"effort":"medium"},"max_output_tokens":32000,"text":{"format":{"type":"text"}},"tools":[{"type":"browser_search","user_location":null,"search_context_size":null}],"tool_choice":"auto","truncation":"disabled","metadata":{},"groq":null,"temperature":1,"top_p":1,"user":null,"service_tier":"default","background":false,"error":null,"incomplete_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":333947,"input_tokens_details":{"cached_tokens":23552},"output_tokens":2412,"output_tokens_details":{"reasoning_tokens":1156},"total_tokens":336359},"parallel_tool_calls":true,"store":false,"top_logprobs":null,"max_tool_calls":null}}

